<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="290" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the British Foreign Secretary</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Eden</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d290fn1">Sent to the
                                    United States Naval Attaché, London, via Navy channels.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-11">August 11,
                                        1943</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Personal and secret to Winant for Eden from the President.</p>
                            <p>I fully approve <gloss target="#t_FNP1">Former Naval Person</gloss>’s
                                proposed reply to Badoglio’s emissary Berio in Tangier as
                                recommended by you.<note n="2" xml:id="d290fn2">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>. Eden sent the approved
                                    instructions to Tangier on August 13, 1943, on which date a copy
                                    of them was sent to Hull by the British Embassy at Washington
                                    (740.00119 European War 1939/1578).</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>